</p><p class="- topic/p ">It is not possible to find the IP address of the machine on the operator panel. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Also the Settings Editor cannot be used as the IP is not known. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">What to do</b> 
</p><table class="- topic/table " id="GUID-A9A7ECDE-6328-4625-8404-AA029EC293AD"><tgroup class="- topic/tgroup " cols="2"><colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*"/><colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*"/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Start zero SDS. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Open ADAM. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> Via the menus: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Collect -&gt; settings &amp; counters -&gt; controller-&gt;settingsinfo-&gt; settings-&gt; configuration-&gt;connectivity-&gt;TCP/IP-&gt;ipv4 address you can find the currently assigned IP address. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Alternative</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> An alternative is to request the customer IT department to use a network scanner tool at the customer. 
